commit_message: Initial add. Non-functional but getting close enough to start committing on.
Improvements to ModelResource and previously broken code.
Some bits of serialization. Still not nearly enough.
Recent modifications to underlying Representation behavior now reflected in the Resource.
BECAUSE LICENSE FILES ARE HARD.
I copy-paste (from my own code) with the worst of them.
Filch, pillage and plunder.
Let's try actually handling PUT now.
Removed a bit that should have left a long time ago.
Added what will eventually become the HTML browse bits.
Added lxml and pyyaml to the README.
Added initial ignores.
Added some basic, initial tests. Need much, much more.
Started testing Representation.
Copying fields rather than using the class-level instances turns out to be important.
Hydrate now does the right thing, instead of the stupid thing.
All ``ModelRepresentation`` bits tested, though ``create`` still fails.
Fixed ``ModelRepresentation.create`` when a callable is involved.
Configuration/utility bits of ``Resource`` are now tested.
Whoo! GETs now work. Working on the remaining methods.
POST/PUT/DELETE operations now work as well.
Changed the way the view methods get wrapped.
Now ships with a functional example!
``setup.py`` is hard, let's go shopping!
Adjust PYTHONPATH in test runner to allow running tests without installing.
Convert ModelRepresentation.get_list to class method.
Added the initial authentication bits.
Merge branch 'master' of github.com:toastdriven/django-tastypie
Missed files committing authentication. :(
Removed old ``example/api.py``. Thanks to jefftriplett for pointing that out.
Bumped the version number a bit.
Added ``Representation.__getattr__`` to make field accesses a little more convenient.
Fields now have more comprehensive tests.
Added a rough ``Api`` class for collecting all resources together.
Update TODO file.
Made note of invalid password string in example fixture data.

Several fixes to BasicAuthentication including moving from returning False to returning HttpUnauthorized with a properly set WWW-Authenticate header, split the HTTP_AUTHORIZATION header in to its two parts, and default to authenticating against all configured AUTHENTICATION_BACKENDS instead of ModelBackend.  BasicAuthentication now works in the browser.
Removed uneccesary import.
Updated authentication tests to check for new HttpUnauthorized behavior and send correct headers.
Added test for WWW-Authenticate header.
Updated resource tests for basic auth.
Add JSONP serialization and serializer options.
Add callback name to serializer options if request is for JSONP.
Add JSONP validation with HttpBadRequest (400) returned on validation error. Thanks to Tav for the validation code.
Use None in method declarations to avoid mutability side effects.
Add deserialize method to resource object as an overridable hook.
Added initial related (FK & M2M) fields.Needs integration testing and general improvements, but it's a start.
Merge branch 'master' of github.com:toastdriven/django-tastypie
Oops, this method receives data for a reason.
Merge branch 'jsonp'

Heavily revamped all urlpatterns created by the ``Api`` and ``Resource``.This should pave the way for ``Representations`` to be able to both provide a URI for themselves as well as be able to take anURI and hydrate themselves off it.
Altered the ``ForeignKey`` & ``ManyToManyField`` fields so they can properly build & parse URIs for sub-representations.
Updated the example code slightly.
Killed completed TODO items.
Missed a ``NotImplementedError``.
Simple pagination via ``limit``/``offset`` in place.
Allow get_list to accept kwargs for __init__ and add instances to returned representations.

New-style JSON serialization.- Can serialize representations and other datatypes.n- Uses RFC2822 style datetime strings.n- Recursive method allows overriding serialization of specific types in Serializer subclasses.
XML serialization support.- Add recursive to_etree method to the serializer that returns an lxml etree element.n- Add deep serialization tests.
Add XML declarations.
Update TODO.
Added basic canonical support.
Allow get_list to accept kwargs for __init__ and add instances to returned representations.

New-style JSON serialization.- Can serialize representations and other datatypes.n- Uses RFC2822 style datetime strings.n- Recursive method allows overriding serialization of specific types in Serializer subclasses.n
XML serialization support.- Add recursive to_etree method to the serializer that returns an lxml etree element.n- Add deep serialization tests.n
Add XML declarations.
Update TODO.
Added missing import to example representations.
Added unhandled kwarg to top_level Api view (which was required to get the example working).  It comes with a FIXME because it doesn't feel quite right.
Add type strings to XML serialized output (so deserializer can convert back to original).
Remove unused argument from get_resource_uri method call.
Add basic XML deserialization.
Merge remote branch 'toastdriven/master'Conflicts:ntTODOnttastypie/serializers.pynttests/core/tests/serializers.pyn
Remove redundant method (added during merge conflict).
More work on related fields. URL reversal now works correctly for related representations.
Related fields now dehydrate correctly.
Added ``readonly`` to fields.
Added type hints to fields.Necessary for coming schema bits as well as potentially useful for serialization.
Basic schema view in place.
More info passed via the schema.
Add expected api_name argument to get_schema view.
Remove unused line.
Add round-trip tests for json and xml.
Move example app into tests directory as basic. Set up to be able to run tests.
Allocated outstanding tasks in the TODO.
Slightly more descriptive output when running all tests.
Added bulk fetch.
Added HTTP method & auth checks to ``get_schema`` & ``get_multiple``.
Fixed invalid kwargs being past to detail views.
Altered the way we spit out out class representations.
Added an ``include_resource_uri`` option to ``Representation``.
Add complex test app.
Merge branch 'master' of github.com:toastdriven/django-tastypie
Reorganized code and added basic ``Paginator`` support.Needs further fleshing out and tests.

Significantly refactored the internals of ``Resource``.Less ``obj_id``-specific, more flexible and more hooks. Needs more tests (for the new methods) as well as some Real-Lifeu00e2u0084u00a2 integration testing before merging.
Added tests for the new ``Resource`` methods.
Cleaned up missed ``**kwargs`` and added ``delete_list`` to ``ModelRepresentation``.
Stubbed out implementation for ``Resource.put_list``.Needs tests and perhaps further implementation work.
Fix wrong model in super call. Add path to filepath field and media root to settings file.
Add sites app, change how installed_apps are edited.
Add basic initial data fixture for complex test app.
Added basic pluggable caching plumbing.
Added pluggable throttling.Still needs full integration tests.
Merge branch 'master' of github.com:toastdriven/django-tastypie
Changed the throttle's HTTP status.Paint a bikeshed and someone will want it a different color. :)
Added throttle integration tests and fixed off-by-one error.
Integrated caching into ``Resource``.No invalidation integrated ATM.
Remove content-types from complex data fixture (unique constraints kill fixture loader until we get natural keys in django 1.2)
Added tests for ``Resource.put_list``.
Fixed an introspection bug when only ``blank=True`` is provided on a ``Model``.
Cleaned up most of the ``FIXME/TODO`` portions of the code.
Add `RepresentationSet` class.
Add RepresentationSet TestCase, add slicing operation to __len__ in RepresentationSet
Use copy instead of deepcopy.
Fixed the ``setup.py`` to incorporate the ``utils`` part of the package.

Add better pagination- Add resource_uri generation to RepresentationSetn- Add `total_count`, `previous`, and `next` values to paginator outputn- Namespace pagination data into `meta` attributen- Add test case for `Paginator` classn
Docstring bomb, part I.
Move to RFC2822-style date and time formatting in serializer.
Add HTTP test server testcase base class and simple test exercising it.
Add more HTTP end-to-end tests. Switch to using file-based test database as HTTP tests fail on in-memory sqlite databases.
Add user representation to basic test application.
Use request.raw_post_data instead of request._raw_post_data (_raw_post_data is a cache).
Use TransactionTestCase as base for TestServerTestCase (thread cannot use transactions).
Add HTTP POST test to basic HTTP test case.
Handle the case where multiple objects may be returned on a ``get``.
Use ``json`` for those with Python 2.6+.
Add smarter test data loader that loads fixtures and sets the correct content type ids for comments.
Add OneToOneField and ManyToOneField (stubs basically, but they seem to work for now)
Fix yaml serialization (preprocess datastructure with to_simple).
Add related fields to complex example representations
Add related field serialization support
Merge branch 'master' of github.com:toastdriven/django-tastypie
Fix error in tests (wrong module name)
Added filtering support.

BACKWARD-INCOMPATIBLE: Massive refactoring, including unifying ``Resource`` & ``Representation``.You will have to update your code (mostly copy-paste old code from ``Representation`` into ``Resource``). Look to the ``basic/complex`` apps in ``tests/`` for an example of how to migrate.nnThis ought to be the last major change before 1.0 and was dictated by actual usage of ``Resource/Representation``.
Bumped revision due to the significance of the previous commit.
Fixed a bug in fields where ``readonly`` was missing from relational fields.
Added a ``FileField`` that tries to properly form media-based URLs.
Terminology fixes.
Adapted the leftover ``Representation`` tests back into the ``Resource`` tests.
TODO cleanup.
More terminology fixes.
Fixed an import error when using an older Django. Thanks to mdornseif for the original patch.
Fixed a bug where ``mimeparse`` may choose the wrong content type when ``*/*`` is given. Thanks to mdornseif for the original patch.
Doing the sane thing and relying on ``pk`` instead of ``id``. Thanks to mdornseif for the patch.
Fixed a bug where dates/datetimes couldn't round-trip properly. Thanks to jefftriplett for the report.
Changed all URL-related references to ``obj_id`` to ``pk``, which unifies the way data is accessed/filtered.
Fixed tests to use ``pk``.
Changed ``Resource`` to allow ``RelatedField`` to be self-referential.Also added a test case that demonstrates that subclassing ``ModelResource`` fails.
Added the ability to include ``absolute_url`` automatically on ``ModelResource`` objects.
Filtering now explicitly errors when an invalid filter is applied.
Better data passing on ``dehydrate/hydrate``.
Altered filtering to allow traversing relations with less code.If you were using 'all' before, you'll need to now use the ``ALL`` constant.
Moved the ``build_filters`` implementation to ``ModelResource``, as it no longer makes sense in the context of ``Resource``.
Added basic sorting capabilities to ``ModelResource``.
Fixed subclassing ``Resource`` & ``ModelResource``.
Fixed self-referential fields to pick the correct ``Resource`` class when using inheritance.
Lightly refactored the internals of ``Resource`` to use exceptions better and smaller override-able methods for common tasks.
Removed reliance on ``pk`` in ``obj_get/obj_delete``.
Added a test for the default format used in serialization.
Fixed a bug in ``DateField/DateTimeField`` where ``dateutil`` would attempt to parse ``None`` and fail miserably. Thanks to jefftriplett for the report.
Fixed a bug where related M2M objects may not be saved prior to being associated to the data being sent. Thanks to jefftriplett for the original patch.
Fixed a bug in ``FileField`` where no data is provided. Thanks to jefftriplett for the report.
Added a couple more ``hydrate``-related tests.
Docstring bomb, part 2.
Fixed a bug in ``Paginator`` when more query parameters are present.
Docstring bomb, part 3. One more to go.
Added a ``.gitignore``.
Added tutorial docs, plus the structure for the rest of the docs.
Ignored a test DB.
Docstring bomb, part 4.Everything that needs a docstring should have at least a basic description now.
Bumped revision. v0.8.0.
Change requires from python-dateutil to python_dateutil which was causing setup.py egg_info to fail.
Added ``ApiKeyAuthentication``.Requires the ``uuid`` library (present in 2.5+, download-able for 2.4.X).n
Added to the README. v0.8.1
Changed TODO to remove ``ApiKeyAuthentication`` and shuffle.
Fixed the formatting of the ``README.rst``.
Changed things so that defining ``resource_name`` is now optional.
Bumped version to v0.8.2.
Ignored ``.buildinfo``.
Django 1.1/1.2 compatibility fixes.

Add authorization (permissions) support including django.contrib.auth permissions.- BACKWARDS INCOMPATIBLE: renamed ``auth_check`` to ``is_authenticated``.n- Three new authorization classes:n- Authorizationn- ReadOnlyAuthorizationn- DjangoAuthorizationn- ResourceOptions._meta needed some changes to allow descriptors to work.n
Correct mistakes in tests.
Add user object to request during authentication stage, require presence in DjangoAuthorization.
Add primary_key attribute to fields.- Related field lookups should try to look up first by primary key and falln  back to creating new resources.n
Make representations not ignore primary keys.
Added a test to ensure that QuerySet results aren't being inadvertently cached.
Allow slashes and alphanumeric characters in primary keys
allow dashes, too
Allow dashes in pk
Clean-up to get the alphanumeric tests fixed. v0.8.3
Fixed a bug where introspected ``TextField``s wouldn't have empty string as a default.
Fixed a bug where a nullable ``OneToOneField`` could blow up if when null. Thanks to coleifer for the original patch.
Modify method for looking up related data so `unique` fields are used as keys to find related objects. Concept of `primary_key` removed in favor of `unique`.
Exception handling to prevent ApiFieldErrors from stopping the request. Fall back to using raw kwargs.
Better exception handling on deletes so as not to obscure errors. Thanks sebleier for the patch!
Fixed docs to use ``api_name`` correctly. Thanks acdha for the patch!

Better error reporting for missing fieldsPreviously the current_object value would be overwritten prior tongenerating the error message, causing it to display something like:nnApiFieldError: The model 'None' has an empty attributen'get_absolute_url' and doesn't allow a default or null value.n
Enabled InterSphinx
Added a recipe for customizing return valuesSimple example showing how to add custom values to repliesn
Added some basic filtering docs
Added class reference autodocAmong other things, this allows the more usable documentation tonreference the class details without repetition.n
Updated tutorial to convert class references into links
Minor README edits.
Merge branch 'master' of http://github.com/toastdriven/django-tastypie into docs
Recommend a newer version of mimeparse.
Fixed the tutorial mention on how to hook up individual resources. Thanks to montylounge for pointing this out.
Merge remote branch 'acdha/docs'
Added acdha to the Primary Authors for the documentation bomb.
Added a slightly more helpful message to the default Serializer's ``to_html`` method.Better than a strange exception. Boo me.
Big performance boost when viewing list views powered by QuerySets. Thanks to jonozzz for pointing this out and the original patch!
Added simple requirements file.
Fixed Resource/ModelResource to honor the ``limit`` option in the ``Meta`` class. Patch by dguaraglia, tests by toastdriven.
Oops. Missed attribution.
Added a passing test to ensure Accept headers sent by jQuery are correctly interpreted.
Fixed alphanumeric's tests to run with the suite.
Inner ``Meta`` classes now support inheritance, like Django's do. Thanks to whiteblack for the original patch!
Fixed how mimeparse receives the list of acceptable formats. Thanks to bartels & acdha for the report & for looking into possible solutions.
``Resource`` now accepts multiple sort_by arguments. Thanks to jonozzz for the original patch!
Reverted the doc changes by acdha.Couldn't ever get them built properly and I'm about to overhaul the docsnby hand. Sorry Chris. :(n
Added some basic filtering docs
Added a recipe for customizing return valuesSimple example showing how to add custom values to repliesn
Updated tutorial to convert class references into links
Readded a better comment in constants that was removed by the revert.
Added Who Uses for kicks and giggles.
Doc shuffle.
Fleshed out the index page of the docs.
Added initial ``Resource`` docs. Needs more but is a start.
Added initial docs on the ``Api`` class & usage.
Added initial caching docs.
Added initial docs on authentication & authorization.
Removed unneeded import from example code.
Added initial serialization docs.
Added initial throttling docs.
Bumped version. v0.9.0
Typo'd. Thanks to DanGer for pointing this out!
Ensure that we get a copy of the formats, rather than a reference. Thanks to bartels for the report!
Added epub as an option when generating the docs.
Missed the import of the constants in the resource docs. Thanks to dguaraglia for the original patch!
A performance optimization during the hydrate & dehydrate cycles. Thanks to dguaraglia for the report!
Made the tests for truthiness in filters a little more tolerant. Better for testing & general use.
When unhandled exceptions are raised, Tastypie now returns a serialized response. Check the settings docs for details. Thanks to rainerborene for the suggestion!
Typo'ed the default value if the setting is missing.
Added example to the cookbook of using resource classes in other places of your code. Thanks to bmihelac for the suggestion and original code.
Fixed a bug where not supplying a value to a nullable ``ToManyField`` would blow up.
Added a setting & a little code to allow slashless URLs. Useful for integrating with other systems (like backbone.js). Thanks to marlun for the suggestion!
Fixed docs on ordering.
Updated resource docs to cover resource URIs & reverse relationships.
Added more convenient reverse relations. See docs for details.Also, Django 1.1 is now a minimum requirement.
Split out ``Resource.urls`` into two sub-methods for better override-ability.Hooray for hyphens!
Fixed a typo involved with self-referential fields. Thanks to joshbohde for pointing this out!
Fixed a regression in the paginator causing it to not function when handed a list/tuple. Thanks to traviscline for the report & original patch!
Added the same ``override_urls`` method to ``Api`` that ``Resource`` got.
Added ``NamespacedApi`` & ``NamespacedModelResource`` to play nicely with things (like the admin) which are already namespaced. Thanks to traviscline for the original patch & debugging help!
Removed unused import.
Ignore charset in deserialization format.
AUTHORS adjustments.
Documented the new url override methods.
The ``allowed_methods`` variants now override a little more sanely when mixed & matched.
Removed unnecessary imports.

BACKWARD-INCOMPATIBLE: Unified the way ``Resource`` accesses ``queryset``, added the ability for the ``obj_FOO`` methods to receive the request if available, and added more granularity/hooks to it.This commit is also known as per-user authorization. It also is mostly backward compatible unless you were overriding the affected methods.
Added more cookbook docs about customizing URLs.
Missed attributing part of the last commit to joshbohde.
Fixed the docs & tests usage of ``request.user``. Thanks to gregmuellegger for pointing it out!
BACKWARD-INCOMPATIBLE: Changed the name of the most basic Tastypie exception for consistency. Only incompatible if you used it to create your own exceptions.
Typo'd the inheritance in the docs for custom ``Authentication``.
Added formal validation support. Thanks to dguaraglia for the initial suggestion!
The top-level & schema endpoints now provide more information about what is there.
Added __unicode__ to ApiKey model.

Added an ApiKeyInline class to be able to easily add it to a custom UserAdmin, e.g.:from django.contrib.auth.models import Usernfrom django.contrib.auth.admin import UserAdminnnfrom tastypie.admin import ApiKeyInlinennclass MyUserAdmin(UserAdmin):ninlines = [ApiKeyInline]nnadmin.site.unregister(User)nadmin.site.register(User, MyUserAdmin)n
Bumped version to v0.9.5.
Updated AUTHORS to include jezdez.
Fixed a missing import in ``admin.py``.
Missing ``()`` in the tutorial. Thanks for the eagle eyes, tomdyson!
Fixed a bug where lazy resource lookups would fail to be able to reverse URLs. Also, fields are now aware of what resource they're hooked up to.
Typo and ambiguous phrasing fixes in the tutorial documentation.
Small edits to settings documentation.
Credited malcolmt in AUTHORS.
BACKWARD-INCOMPATIBLE: Switch default datetime/date/time formatting back to ISO-8601. If you preferred the RFC-2822 formatting, check the settings docs for a way to restore this format.
Added debugging docs, with the first entry being about XML in the browser.
Fixed handling of ``ApiFieldError``s to provide useful messages back to the user, instead of leaving them in the dark about what they did wrong. Thanks to gregmuellegger for pointing this out!
Changed the ``Paginator`` so that passing ``limit=0`` as a query parameter fetches all results.
Fixed ``Resource`` to send ``Cache-Control: no-cache`` when a request is made via Ajax to accommodate IE. Thanks to joshbohde for the report!
Unified the way data is converted to strings & fixed a bug where doing ``**kwargs`` on that data would fail. Thanks to adamfast for the report!
No really. Fixed the passing of data to **kwargs, dammit.
Raise AttributeError in __getattr__() when an attribute isn't found
Changed URL parameter for ordering to ``order_by`` (was ``sort_by``). This change is backward-compatible.

Kwargs passed to ``obj_get_list`` now work as filters, as they were always supposed to. This allows specifying filter data as part of the URL. Thanks to ericholscher & joshbohde for pointing this out!
On ``NotFound``, Tastypie now sends the correct status code (404) and will no longer send error emails (unless ``SEND_BROKEN_LINK_EMAILS`` is set). Thanks to ericholscher for the report!
Fixed ``DeprecationWarning`` due to old-style syntax. Thanks to acdha for the itteh-bitteh patch committeh!
Allowed fields to pick up ``help_text`` from the model's fields where available. Thanks to onyxfish for the patch!
Fixed the metaclasses so that ``Resource`` no longer looks for a ``queryset``. Thanks to hensom for the patch!
Automatically handle HTTP OPTIONS.
Added tests for OPTIONS on resources.

Stripped off the automatic MEDIA_URL prefixing.This breaks Django's support for using custom storage backends for filesnand images.  If not otherwise specified, Django's default storage is setnup to include the MEDIA_URL prefix already, so this should not breaknany existing code.n

Don't rely on the __unicode__ implementation for FileFields.Instead, just take the url attribute value, which is always what younwant to see in the dehydrated output.  This makes the implementationnindependent of the storage backend that is used.n
Allow fields to have no associated file with them.In these cases, value is not None, but refers to an empty FileFieldnobject.n
Made a couple further fixes on ``FileField`` changes.
Added ``install_requires`` to satisfy setuptools. Thanks to reinout for the report!
Released v0.9.6.
Started 0.9.7-beta.
Added support for JSONP to the `top_level` view in the Api.
Added documentation about non-ORM resources.
Fleshed out docs on the request/response cycle.

Added test case to demonstrate that data that should not be overwrittable can be overwritten. Thanks to Greg McGuire for the report & joshbodhe for the patch.A followup commit will stop this behavior.n
Fixed an issue where data could be overwritten on a read-only resource. Thanks again to Greg McGuire for the report!
Resource.full_hydrate can now set an attribute with a previous non-None value to None, if the field has null set to True.
Added missing docstrings.
basic.html template fixdjango-vacuum pointed out that this for loop was missing an endforn
Catch ValidationErrors that may have bubbled up, and return a BadRequest instead.
Added tests for catching ValidationError and returning BadRequest.
Fixed a previous change that got accidentally overwritten.
Made the ``Paginator`` swappable.
Bumped version. v0.9.7
Started 0.9.8-beta.
BACKWARD-INCOMPATIBLE: Filtering now ensures that fields on related are filterable. Another side effect is that filters now use the ``Resource`` field name instead of the database field name.
Added docs on the fields provided by Tastypie. Thanks to veselosky for the original patch!
Fixed a bug where nullable ``ToOneField``s could error during ``full_hydrate``. Thanks to adamfast for the report!
Added splitting on commas for range and in filters.
Fixed the required version of dateutil to *NOT* use the Python 3 version. Thanks to kmike for the catch & the patch!
Added Read the Docs to Who Uses.
Fixed a missing import. Thanks to entequak for pointing it out!
Added Luzme to Who Uses.
Added cookbook documentation on adding search to a resource.
Raise AttributeError with the missing attribute name

Fixed test_apply_sorting relation test to use a column thats actually sortable.All usernames are the same so sorting on those doesn't make much sensenas every database behaves differently in that case.  Using the __id fieldnalso tests the related column sorting but uses a valid sorting columnnthats testable as the result before this test was kinda undefined.n
Added EnTeQuAk to AUTHORS.
I was getting the error message Bundle' object does not support item assignmentI changed the order and it works as expected now.n
Split up a fallback that could have ill side effects. Thanks to alex for pointing this out!
Removed an error-prone test that gives inconsistent results across versions of Django.

Pulled ``apply_authorization_limits`` out of ``get_object_list`` & rearranged the ordering on how it gets called. Thanks to dbpatterson for pointing this out!This doesn't affect existing authorization checks that change the ``QuerySet``, but if an attribute is being checked per-object, this greatly reduces the set of objects to be processed.
Added a note about ``WSGIPassAuthorization`` to the docs. Thanks to dhageman for pointing this out!
Return HTTP 400 Bad Request for invalid filters
Updated the README.

Tweak HTTP response code for invalid querystring filtersThis changes the response code from 404 to 400 when you provide an invalidnquerystring filter: e.g. /book/?author=douglas-adams rather thann/book/?author=42n
Fix description of detail_allowed_methods.
Cookbook example for per-user resources.
Added novel to AUTHORS.
Fixed a bug where ``obj_get`` & friends wouldn't have a ``QuerySet`` to work with. Thanks to helgikrs for pointing this out!
Fixed an ugly bare ``except`` in ``put_detail``. Thanks to dlrust for the report!
Added support for default values on ``RelatedField``s. Thanks to dhageman for the original patch!
Added dhageman to AUTHORS.
The ``ToManyField`` can now accept a callable for ``attribute``, allowing filtering of reverse relations. Thanks to rwillmer for starting this train of thought!
Removed some needlessly duplicated code from ``fields.py``.
Added a ``DecimalField``, ``ListField`` & ``DictField``.
Documented another approach to nesting resources.
Added hooks for massaging data before serialization & after deserialization.
Added docs on interacting with Tastypie using curl.
Added South migrations.
Added ``DigestAuthentication``. Thanks to thepeopleseason for finishing the digest work I started & getting it tested/doc'd!
Fixed docs on registering ``Resource`` instances with the ``Api``.
Fixed a bug in hydration to respect ``attribute`` first, falling back to ``instance_name``.
Fixed a typo in the ``Interacting`` docs. Thanks to DanGer for the catch!
Bumped to v0.9.9!
Added TimeField.
Added jesperp to AUTHORS.
Bumped version for beta.
Removed the automatic creation of ``ApiKey`` & documented the ``create_api_key`` function.
Fixed a bug in the test suite related to removing the automatic ``ApiKey`` bits. Thanks to thepeopleseason for the original patch!
Improved the tests on the ``Resource.alter_*`` methods to be more clear about how they work. Thanks to onyxfish for the report!
Fixed typos and ambiguous phrasings in the tutorial documentation.
Fixed a bug with Unicode data in the request parameters.
Cleaned up two ReST errors.
Fixed a bug where a ``ToOneField`` couldn't be set to ``None``. Thanks to MacMaru for the report & the original patch!
The ``__in`` filter can now accept the preferred ``tags__in=foo&tags__in=bar`` in addition to ``tags__in=foo,bar``. Thanks to jonozz & traviscline for the suggestion & discussion.
Added ``blank=True`` option to allow the user to omit otherwise-required data. Thanks to adamfast & MacMaru for the report!
Added tests to help demonstrate the regression & need for ``blank=True``.
Committed changes missed by the previous commit.
Added a camelCase serializer to the cookbook. Thanks to ulmus for the code!
Fixed URL resolution to handle script prefix.
Fixed test failures related to looking up attribute values.
Added zbyte64 to AUTHORS.
Add test for creating related ForeignKey resources from data dictionary
Fixed a bug where non-M2M related data might not be updated with the rest of the request. Thanks to claymation for the report & the tests!
Spruced up the cookbook example on camelCase. Thanks to EnTeQuAk for the patch.
Added tox to the mix.
BACKWARD-INCOMPATIBLE: Fixed HTTP status codes to be more correct. Mostly this means failed gets/deletes issue a 404 (instead of 410) now. Thanks to jacobian for the report!
Added ``request`` (if available) to all bundles to make request-dependent changes easier through the code.
Added binary plist support, which yield super-fast parsing on iOS devices. Thanks to jacobian for the suggestion!
Improved the exception handling to use logging where available & only manually send errors on Django <1.3. Thanks to cyberdelia for the original patch!
Added cyberdelia to AUTHORS.
Added Politifact to Who Uses!
Added documentation on the dehydrate/hydrate cycles in Tastypie. (Finally!)
Added a long-overdue note to the tutorial about how to enable POST/PUT/DELETE.
Fixed the tox file to test the right things. Thanks to EnTeQuAk for the original patch!
Added a note about where to look on the plist support (and see the awesome benchmark graph).
Added the ``readonly`` kwarg to the ``ToOneField/ToManyField``. Thanks to coleifer for the report!
Removed uses of ``isinstance``, which could cause things to fail when Tastypie is namespaced differently. Thanks to indro for the report!Also: Quack quack.
Fixed DecimalField unittest to properly test for the right value & be assoicated with the right field type.
Missed committing the removal of an ``isinstance`` check.
Fixed the case where a related object could be ``blank=True``. Thanks to MacMaru for the original patch!
Added a ``always_return_data`` option, which will populate the bodies of POST/PUT responses. Thanks to cyberdelia for the original patch!

Handle malformed HTTP Accept valuesSome clients cause tastypie to return a 500 error because they send a requestnwith an HTTP Accept header which contains an invalid MIME type (e.g. any valuenwithout a / other than *, which mimeparse handles).nndetermine_format() now raises BadRequest any time mimeparse fails.nResources now handle this by returning HTTP 400 immediately rather thannthe normal error responsen

BACKWARDS-INCOMPATIBLE: Format Hardening ReleaseFormat Hardening Security Releasenn* XML decoding has been wrapped in the defusedxml libraryn* XML requests may no longer include DTDs by defaultn* Deserialization will return HTTP 400 for any XML decode errorsn* Add `TASTYPIE_DEFAULT_FORMATS` setting to globally restrict the set ofn  supported formats (closes #833)n* Content negotiation will return an error for malformed accept headers (closes #832)n* The Api class itself now allows a custom serializer (closes #817)n* The serialization documentation has been upgraded with security advicennBackwards-incompatible changes:nn* XML serialization:n- defusedxml is now requiredn- defusedxml requires lxml 3 or laternn``pip install defusedxml lxml>=3``n* Python 2.5 is no longer officially supported because defusedxml requiresn  Python 2.6 or later.n

If no object_class is present, do not try to instantiate an object when building the bundle. This does not affect model-based resources; however, the assumption that had been made that an object_class is always going to be present is not valid when using custom Resource objects that are not necessarily model-based.

Removed call to fk_resource.can_update(), since fk_resource.save() will the necessary object permissions checks (authorized_update_detail or authorized_create_detail). can_update() only checks the HTTP methods allowed, which doesn't really make sense for related resources. This fixes a bug (PR #1344) in otherwise updatable related resources which had PUT disabled. The bug caused the related resource to overwrite existing columns in the DB, since missing values were set to default since full hydration hadn't taken place.Also includes changes to prevent saving bundles loaded via URI, and to make sure data is only saved inside Resource classes (replaced calls to obj_update() in RelatedField().resource_from_data()).n

Importing unicode_literals causes a problem in South when importing from django.db.models.fields because then the name of the model class that is passed into __import__ is unicode, rather than a byte string. I'm not quite sure why this causes a problem importing from this module but not others. However, removing the unicode_literals import from these migrations fixes the issue, and it doesn't look like the migrations have any literals that need to be unicode.

Update validation (in particular the form_args function) to allow FK relationships to work when using CleanedDataFormValidation with django ORM models that have Related fields (#923)Convert url relationships to pks in form validation.

Update validation (in particular the form_args function) to allow FK relationships to work when using CleanedDataFormValidation with django ORM models that have Related fieldsFormerly, when an insert or update operation occurs on a model that uses a FK relationship field in the form, TastyPie would pass into the form validation the URI that was provided in bundle.data.  Unfortunately, Django really wants a PK reference (the output of model_to_dict, in this case) and would fail in such cases.  This fix detects those related fields in the target model (bundle.obj) and leaves the references to the related table intact, but still applies bundle values for all other fields (some of which might not be in the model, but might be required for the form.)n
